update_metric_definition(25.10)                update_metric_definition(25.10)

Name  update_metric_definition  -  Updates  the specified properties of an al-
       ready-existing metric definition with the same name
Syntax
Parameters -compare <compareFunction> Specifies the compare  function,  [more-
       Better|lessBetter|moreBetterBelowTarget|lessBetterAboveTarget].     The
       comparison options show the good or bad color when the value  is  below
       or  above  the target value as appropriate. Data_type: string, optional
       -description  <metricDescription> Specifies the description of the met-
       ric. Data_type: string, optional -id <databaseID> Specifies  the  data-
       base  ID. Data_type: string, optional -inheritance_tcl <TclName> Speci-
       fies Tcl for combining children values. The metric is not  executed  in
       the   global   namespace.  The  equivalent  proc  args  is  {children}.
       Data_type: string, optional -name <metric_name > Specifies the name  of
       the  metric.  Data_type:  string, required -no_inheritance Disables the
       inheritance of the metric. Data_type: bool, optional  -help  Outputs  a
       brief  description  that includes type and default information for each
       update_metric_definition parameter. For a detailed description  of  the
       command and all of its parameters, use the man command: man update_met-
       ric_definition -precision <number_of_decimal_places> Specifies the num-
       ber  of  decimal  places.  Data_type:  int, optional Default: 0 -target
       <metric_name> Specifies the target or the name of metric containing the
       target value. Data_type: string, optional -tcl {  <TCL_command_list>  }
       Specifies  the  list  of  TCL commands or proc to generate (return) the
       metric which is of the format {<value> <unit>}. Data_type: string,  op-
       tional  -threshold <reporting_unit> Specifies the threshold for compar-
       ing numbers in HTML. If the delta between the two  numbers  being  com-
       pared  is  less than the threshold then the metric will be colored yel-
       low. If it is outside the threshold, then it is colored  red  or  green
       depending  on  the compare function i.e. whether more is better or less
       is better. Data_type: string, optional -tools  <listOfTools>  Specifies
       the  list  of  tools in which the tcl code will run. Data_type: string,
       optional -type <metricType> Specifies the type  of  metric.  Data_type:
       string, optional The various metrics types are:
